-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

Not all text is ASCII. Files can be encoded in many different formats. UTF-16 stores each character as 16 bits instead of 8, which is why the file looked like random symbols when read normally.

When a file looks like gibberish, that is a clue not a dead end. Think about what encoding might have been used and work backwards from there.

Python is extremely powerful for encoding and decoding tasks. The encode() and decode() methods let you convert between character encodings easily.

Indentation in Python is mandatory. Two spaces or one tab before code inside a loop is required or Python will throw an error.

The challenge name Transformation was itself a hint. When you see that word in a CTF, think about encoding and decoding.
